7. The deep philosophical conclusion

At the deepest level, many modern theories suggest something surprising:

The universe may not fundamentally consist of things with properties.

Instead it may consist of relationships and structures, and what we call properties are features of those relationships.

⸻

A compact way to say it

Potential isn’t stored in something.

It is the structure of the situation itself.

